WEBVTT

00:00:07.173 --> 00:00:09.275
DAN (VOICEOVER): After the Gundalians hijacked Bakugan

00:00:09.376 --> 00:00:11.177
Interspace and forced us out, things

00:00:11.277 --> 00:00:13.980
took a turn for the worse in the battle for Neathia.

00:00:14.080 --> 00:00:16.616
We decided to join Fabia as she returned home so we

00:00:16.716 --> 00:00:18.017
could help with the fight.

00:00:18.118 --> 00:00:20.887
Once we got there, we were made members of the Castle Knights.

00:00:20.987 --> 00:00:23.123
Now earth and Neathia were united in the struggle

00:00:23.223 --> 00:00:25.658
to keep Barodius from stealing the Sacred Orb.

00:00:25.759 --> 00:00:29.195
Lucky for us, we have the most powerful Bakugan, Dragonoid

00:00:29.295 --> 00:00:31.431
Colossus, on our side.

00:00:31.531 --> 00:00:33.032
Now, Drago.

00:00:33.133 --> 00:00:34.100
Bakugan brawl!

00:00:34.200 --> 00:00:35.402
[THEME - DANIEL LEBLANC &amp; CREIGHTON DOANE,

00:00:35.502 --> 00:00:36.336
\"TWO WORLDS COLLIDE\"]

00:00:36.436 --> 00:00:38.571
THEME SONG: What are you gonna do?

00:00:38.671 --> 00:00:41.975
The odds are stacked against you.

00:00:42.075 --> 00:00:44.010
Back against the wall.

00:00:44.110 --> 00:00:47.080
Gotta give it your all.

00:00:47.180 --> 00:00:50.283
This is the final stand.

00:00:50.383 --> 00:00:51.951
The power's in your hands.

00:00:52.051 --> 00:00:54.788
Two worlds collide on the inside.

00:00:57.657 --> 00:01:03.430
You gotta fight for what's right before it's gone, gone, gone.

00:01:03.530 --> 00:01:05.365
This is Bakugan.

00:01:05.465 --> 00:01:06.366
[intense music]

00:01:06.466 --> 00:01:07.367
Hey!

00:01:07.467 --> 00:01:08.334
Ah!

00:01:08.435 --> 00:01:10.336
Leave her alone.

00:01:10.437 --> 00:01:11.304
Huh?

00:01:11.404 --> 00:01:12.305
Barodius!

00:01:24.984 --> 00:01:26.786
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): Greetings.

00:01:26.886 --> 00:01:29.989
I am Code Eve.

00:01:30.089 --> 00:01:32.258
The mother light of all Bakugan.

00:01:36.162 --> 00:01:38.498
[theme music]

00:01:38.598 --> 00:01:43.303
DAN (VOICEOVER): Bakugan Battle Brawlers in \"Destiny Revealed.\"

00:01:43.403 --> 00:01:46.005
Code Eve, huh?

00:01:46.106 --> 00:01:47.740
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): Yes, that is what she said.

00:01:47.841 --> 00:01:50.710
Why am I feeling so uneasy and on edge?

00:01:50.810 --> 00:01:55.381
It's strange, but I've had this feeling before.

00:01:55.482 --> 00:01:57.183
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): I am the light force

00:01:57.283 --> 00:01:58.618
inside the Sacred Orb.

00:01:58.718 --> 00:01:59.619
What?

00:01:59.719 --> 00:02:01.554
Does this mean the Sacred Orb is just

00:02:01.654 --> 00:02:03.022
a shell for the true power?

00:02:03.122 --> 00:02:04.324
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): In the beginning

00:02:04.424 --> 00:02:08.228
there were two dragons, one of fire, one of darkness,

00:02:08.328 --> 00:02:12.465
Dragonoid and Dharaknoid, and their DNA was comprised

00:02:12.565 --> 00:02:15.068
of genetic material from the most powerful living

00:02:15.168 --> 00:02:17.203
organism, the Ultimate Warrior.

00:02:17.303 --> 00:02:19.772
So Nurzak's ramblings were true.

00:02:19.873 --> 00:02:20.673
DHARAK (VOICEOVER): Quiet.

00:02:20.773 --> 00:02:22.275
Let her speak.

00:02:22.375 --> 00:02:23.843
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): Unfortunately, the powers

00:02:23.943 --> 00:02:25.912
of the original two were too strong

00:02:26.012 --> 00:02:28.381
and caused the dimension to split into two.

00:02:28.481 --> 00:02:31.584
The force of the separation caused some residual energy

00:02:31.684 --> 00:02:34.687
to scatter, which led to a different kind of creation.

00:02:34.787 --> 00:02:35.822
Isn't that--

00:02:35.922 --> 00:02:37.323
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): New Vestroia.

00:02:37.423 --> 00:02:38.525
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): The dimension

00:02:38.625 --> 00:02:42.295
in which Dragonoid lived quickly separated into six

00:02:42.395 --> 00:02:46.466
distinct attribute worlds.

00:02:46.566 --> 00:02:49.135
The dimension in which Dharaknoid lived

00:02:49.235 --> 00:02:51.304
saw the creation of only two worlds.

00:02:56.109 --> 00:02:56.943
Of course.

00:02:57.043 --> 00:02:58.845
Neathia and Gundalia.

00:02:58.945 --> 00:03:00.613
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): In the millennia that followed,

00:03:00.713 --> 00:03:04.384
each dimension created their own origin legends as they built

00:03:04.484 --> 00:03:06.119
their respective histories.

00:03:06.219 --> 00:03:08.388
As more and more time passed, it seemed

00:03:08.488 --> 00:03:11.157
that the original two were destined to never meet again.

00:03:11.257 --> 00:03:14.861
That is, until Princess Fabia of Neathia

00:03:14.961 --> 00:03:16.896
sent out a distress call for help

00:03:16.996 --> 00:03:18.798
in fighting off Gundalian invaders,

00:03:18.898 --> 00:03:20.867
and the Battle Brawlers responded.

00:03:20.967 --> 00:03:23.536
This led to the eventual meeting of Drago and Dharak,

00:03:23.636 --> 00:03:27.173
the two Bakugan who inherited the original Bakugan DNA.

00:03:27.273 --> 00:03:29.976
Because they both possess the genes of the original Bakugan,

00:03:30.076 --> 00:03:31.744
I was instantly concerned.

00:03:31.844 --> 00:03:34.747
If they were to engage in battle there was a strong possibility

00:03:34.847 --> 00:03:36.683
that they would split the dimension again,

00:03:36.783 --> 00:03:38.751
just like their ancestors had.

00:03:38.851 --> 00:03:41.754
This is why I continually intervened and attempted

00:03:41.854 --> 00:03:45.124
to keep them from battling, but then the war between Gundalia

00:03:45.224 --> 00:03:47.961
and Neathia came to a head and the forbidden power

00:03:48.061 --> 00:03:50.663
possessed by the dark Bakugan was unleashed.

00:03:50.763 --> 00:03:55.001
It caused tremendous devastation and nearly destroyed Neathia.

00:03:55.101 --> 00:03:57.670
The simple fact is that Drago and Dharak have both

00:03:57.770 --> 00:04:00.006
been endowed with the powers of the Ultimate Warrior,

00:04:00.106 --> 00:04:02.942
yet they exist on the opposite ends of the spectrum,

00:04:03.042 --> 00:04:04.944
just like shadow and light.

00:04:05.044 --> 00:04:07.680
I understand now that trying to keep them separated

00:04:07.780 --> 00:04:09.282
would be fighting the inevitable.

00:04:09.382 --> 00:04:11.651
That Drago and Dharak should meet in battle

00:04:11.751 --> 00:04:15.989
is their destiny, just as it is your destiny, Dan and Barodius.

00:04:16.089 --> 00:04:19.792
Your fates are all inextricably linked.

00:04:19.892 --> 00:04:20.860
Seriously?

00:04:20.960 --> 00:04:23.496
Impossible.

00:04:23.596 --> 00:04:25.098
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): Battlers and their partner

00:04:25.198 --> 00:04:29.369
Bakugan are connected by a bond, known as the Switch Code.

00:04:29.469 --> 00:04:31.938
While Bakugan can fight with any battlers,

00:04:32.038 --> 00:04:35.074
it is only their partners who hold the Switch Code that

00:04:35.174 --> 00:04:36.743
can maximize their potential.

00:04:36.843 --> 00:04:39.112
This is why, Dan, you hold the Switch

00:04:39.212 --> 00:04:42.749
Code for Drago and Barodius you hold that for Dharak.

00:04:42.849 --> 00:04:45.551
Just as Drago and Dharak were destined to battle,

00:04:45.652 --> 00:04:47.754
Dan and Barodius were destined to be

00:04:47.854 --> 00:04:49.422
their partners along the way.

00:04:49.522 --> 00:04:51.391
I always knew it.

00:04:51.491 --> 00:04:54.027
For generations the Gundalian royal family

00:04:54.127 --> 00:04:56.429
has been aware of the bond between battlers

00:04:56.529 --> 00:05:00.700
and their Bakugan, only we called it, The Solidarity.

00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:01.901
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): Dan, I believe

00:05:02.001 --> 00:05:03.603
on earth you would commonly refer

00:05:03.703 --> 00:05:05.838
to such a thing as friendship.

00:05:05.938 --> 00:05:07.507
Whatever it is--

00:05:07.607 --> 00:05:09.075
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): We're connected.

00:05:09.175 --> 00:05:10.410
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): Be that as it may,

00:05:10.510 --> 00:05:12.712
I cannot allow your collective destinies

00:05:12.812 --> 00:05:14.747
to endanger any more innocents.

00:05:14.847 --> 00:05:17.750
That is why I have decided that your final battle will be

00:05:17.850 --> 00:05:20.353
fought in a middle dimension, where no one else can

00:05:20.453 --> 00:05:21.854
get caught in the crossfire.

00:05:21.954 --> 00:05:24.057
This is the battle that will end the war

00:05:24.157 --> 00:05:26.025
between Gundalia and Neathia.

00:05:26.125 --> 00:05:28.828
Does everyone understand what I am telling them?

00:05:28.928 --> 00:05:30.697
100%.

00:05:30.797 --> 00:05:32.632
Absolutely.

00:05:32.732 --> 00:05:33.533
[grunts]

00:05:33.633 --> 00:05:40.506
[grunts]

00:05:40.606 --> 00:05:42.075
CODE EVE (VOICEOVER): The winner of this battle

00:05:42.175 --> 00:05:44.310
will take control of all the Bakugan,

00:05:44.410 --> 00:05:46.979
so make sure that you don't hold anything back.

00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:48.381
Game on, gentlemen.

00:05:48.481 --> 00:05:49.282
OK.

00:05:49.382 --> 00:05:50.717
Let's do this!

00:05:50.817 --> 00:05:52.685
Bakugan brawl!

00:05:52.785 --> 00:05:54.754
Bakugan scan.

00:05:54.854 --> 00:05:56.589
This is for all the marbles.

00:05:56.689 --> 00:05:58.424
Pyrus Blitz Dragonoid!

00:05:58.524 --> 00:06:00.727
Bakugan brawl.

00:06:00.827 --> 00:06:03.129
Bakugan scan.

00:06:03.229 --> 00:06:05.331
Rise Darkus Phantom Dharak.

00:06:05.431 --> 00:06:07.734
DHARAK (VOICEOVER): [roars]

00:06:07.834 --> 00:06:09.802
BARODIUS: Evil Bind.

00:06:09.902 --> 00:06:13.306
Darkness Shaker.

00:06:13.406 --> 00:06:14.207
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): Ah!

00:06:14.307 --> 00:06:16.075
Ahh!

00:06:16.175 --> 00:06:17.210
Drago!

00:06:17.310 --> 00:06:18.811
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): [grunts]

00:06:18.911 --> 00:06:21.748
BARODIUS: High Skewed Shaker!

00:06:21.848 --> 00:06:24.283
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): Ah!

00:06:24.383 --> 00:06:25.651
Ready, Dan?

00:06:25.752 --> 00:06:27.520
Now, Drago!

00:06:27.620 --> 00:06:29.021
Dual Barnum!

00:06:32.024 --> 00:06:33.326
DHARAK (VOICEOVER): [grunts]

00:06:33.426 --> 00:06:35.194
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): Particle Buster!

00:06:35.294 --> 00:06:37.363
DHARAK (VOICEOVER): Is that the best you can do?

00:06:37.463 --> 00:06:38.431
Tempest Shield!

00:06:41.534 --> 00:06:44.003
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): You haven't seen anything yet.

00:06:44.103 --> 00:06:48.374
[roars] Grr.

00:06:48.474 --> 00:06:50.543
Ah!

00:06:50.643 --> 00:06:52.712
DHARAK (VOICEOVER): [roars]

00:06:52.812 --> 00:06:54.647
Finish him!

00:06:54.747 --> 00:06:56.149
Blitz Hammer!

00:06:56.249 --> 00:06:57.617
Get up, Dharak.

00:06:57.717 --> 00:07:00.887
Barrow Laia.

00:07:00.987 --> 00:07:05.525
[grunting]

00:07:05.625 --> 00:07:07.860
BARODIUS: Once we have control of the Bakugan,

00:07:07.960 --> 00:07:10.296
the entire universe will be at our feet.

00:07:10.396 --> 00:07:12.465
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): [grunts]

00:07:12.565 --> 00:07:16.469
Your problem, Dan, is that you have no vision, no master plan.

00:07:16.569 --> 00:07:19.205
You just want to be a good guy, which

00:07:19.305 --> 00:07:22.842
is why having command of all Bakugan is wasted on you.

00:07:22.942 --> 00:07:27.747
I on the other hand, am a completely different story.

00:07:27.847 --> 00:07:29.682
DHARAK (VOICEOVER): [grunts] Grr!

00:07:29.782 --> 00:07:33.653
A boy like you can never be king, not ever.

00:07:33.753 --> 00:07:36.189
As long as I'm alive, you'll never take

00:07:36.289 --> 00:07:37.757
the power of the Sacred Orb.

00:07:37.857 --> 00:07:39.258
That's a lot of tough talk.

00:07:39.358 --> 00:07:41.727
Let's see if you can back it up, pal.

00:07:41.828 --> 00:07:43.496
DHARAK (VOICEOVER): Exodus Shaker!

00:07:43.596 --> 00:07:45.598
[roars]

00:07:45.698 --> 00:07:52.271
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): Spire Dragon [roars]

00:07:52.371 --> 00:07:55.608
[groaning]

00:07:55.708 --> 00:07:56.509
DAN: Drago!

00:07:56.609 --> 00:07:57.777
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): [grunts]

00:07:57.877 --> 00:07:58.678
BARODIUS: Dharak!

00:07:58.778 --> 00:08:00.513
DHARAK (VOICEOVER): [grunts]

00:08:00.613 --> 00:08:03.583
Drago, you gotta get up, pal.

00:08:03.683 --> 00:08:04.483
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): [moans]

00:08:04.584 --> 00:08:06.185
Ah!

00:08:06.285 --> 00:08:09.121
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): [moans] I'll be OK.

00:08:09.222 --> 00:08:11.157
DHARAK (VOICEOVER): Chaos Magnalia!

00:08:11.257 --> 00:08:14.894
You're going down, Drago!

00:08:14.994 --> 00:08:16.128
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): Ahh!

00:08:16.229 --> 00:08:17.129
[groans in pain]

00:08:17.230 --> 00:08:18.030
Ah!

00:08:18.130 --> 00:08:24.103
DRAGO (VOICEOVER): [groans]

00:08:24.203 --> 00:08:27.106
Drago!

00:08:27.206 --> 00:08:28.307
[battle music]

00:08:28.407 --> 00:08:29.642
BARODIUS (VOICEOVER): The power of the Sacred Orb

00:08:29.742 --> 00:08:32.511
will finally be mine, Dharak.

00:08:32.612 --> 00:08:33.880
[battle music]

00:08:33.980 --> 00:08:36.782
DAN (VOICEOVER): Drago, you can't let them win this, buddy.

00:08:36.883 --> 00:08:42.855
[moaning] Huh?

00:08:42.955 --> 00:08:43.856
Huh?

00:08:50.096 --> 00:08:51.864
LINEHALT (VOICEOVER): This isn't what we wanted.

00:08:51.964 --> 00:08:56.035
The life we wanted to live in the sunshine, this is not it,

00:08:56.135 --> 00:08:57.036
not even close.

00:08:59.739 --> 00:09:00.806
Linehalt.

00:09:00.907 --> 00:09:02.174
LINEHALT (VOICEOVER): I think I finally

00:09:02.275 --> 00:09:05.912
understand what I'm supposed to use my forbidden power for.

00:09:06.012 --> 00:09:07.480
[powerful music]

00:09:07.580 --> 00:09:08.481
Oh!

